### =========================
###  AUTHENTICATION TESTS
### =========================

### 1. Unauthorized request (no API key)
GET http://localhost:5112/users
Accept: application/json

### 2. Unauthorized request (invalid API key)
GET http://localhost:5112/users
X-Api-Key: WrongKey123
Accept: application/json

### 3. Authorized request (valid API key)
GET http://localhost:5112/users
X-Api-Key: TechHiveSecretAuthKey123
Accept: application/json



### =========================
###  HAPPY PATH TESTS (Authorized)
### =========================

### Get all users
GET http://localhost:5112/users
X-Api-Key: TechHiveSecretAuthKey123
Accept: application/json

### Get user by ID (existing)
GET http://localhost:5112/users/1
X-Api-Key: TechHiveSecretAuthKey123
Accept: application/json

### Add a new valid user
POST http://localhost:5112/users
X-Api-Key: TechHiveSecretAuthKey123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 3,
  "name": "Charlie",
  "email": "charlie@example.com"
}

### Update an existing user
PUT http://localhost:5112/users/3
X-Api-Key: TechHiveSecretAuthKey123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 3,
  "name": "Charlie Updated",
  "email": "charlie.updated@example.com"
}

### Delete an existing user
DELETE http://localhost:5112/users/3
X-Api-Key: TechHiveSecretAuthKey123



### =========================
###  ERROR CASE TESTS (Authorized)
### =========================

### Get user by ID (non-existent)
GET http://localhost:5112/users/999
X-Api-Key: TechHiveSecretAuthKey123
Accept: application/json

### Add a user with missing name (validation error)
POST http://localhost:5112/users
X-Api-Key: TechHiveSecretAuthKey123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 4,
  "name": "",
  "email": "no.name@example.com"
}

### Add a user with invalid email (validation error)
POST http://localhost:5112/users
X-Api-Key: TechHiveSecretAuthKey123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 5,
  "name": "Invalid Email User",
  "email": "not-an-email"
}

### Add a user with duplicate ID (conflict)
POST http://localhost:5112/users
X-Api-Key: TechHiveSecretAuthKey123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Duplicate ID",
  "email": "duplicate@example.com"
}

### Update a non-existent user (not found)
PUT http://localhost:5112/users/999
X-Api-Key: TechHiveSecretAuthKey123
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 999,
  "name": "Ghost User",
  "email": "ghost@example.com"
}

### Delete a non-existent user (not found)
DELETE http://localhost:5112/users/999
X-Api-Key: TechHiveSecretAuthKey123